        </a>
        
                
        
    </div><!-- end .row-->
</article><!-- #post-## -->

<article id="post-326" class="post-326 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-web">
    <div class="row no-pad">
      
        
        <div class="col-xs-12 col-sm-11 no-pad">
            <header class="entry-header">
                <h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://alexander.kirk.at/2012/02/15/git-tip-changing-your-mind-push-pending-changes-to-a-not-yet-existing-new-branch/" rel="bookmark">Git tip: Changing your mind: Push pending changes to a (not-yet existing) new branch</a></h2>                <div class="entry-meta">
                    <a href=" https://alexander.kirk.at/2012/02/15/git-tip-changing-your-mind-push-pending-changes-to-a-not-yet-existing-new-branch/ "><span class="posted-on"><time class="entry-date published" datetime="2012-02-15T12:30:11+01:00">February 15, 2012</time><time class="updated" datetime="2012-02-15T12:36:53+01:00">February 15, 2012</time> </span></a>
                </div><!-- .entry-meta -->
                            </header><!-- .entry-header -->
            <div class="entry-content">
                
                                        
            <p>It happens quite often to me that I start committing things and only afterwards decide I should have created a new branch.</p>
<p>So <code>git status</code> says something like:</p>
<p><code>Your branch is ahead of 'origin/master' by 4 commits.</code></p>
<p><img data-attachment-id="336" data-permalink="https://alexander.kirk.at/2012/02/15/git-tip-changing-your-mind-push-pending-changes-to-a-not-yet-existing-new-branch/git-branch-1/" data-orig-file="https://alexander.kirk.at/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/git-branch-1.png" data-orig-size="228,105" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;}" data-image-title="git-branch-1" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://alexander.kirk.at/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/git-branch-1.png" data-large-file="https://alexander.kirk.at/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/git-branch-1.png" loading="lazy" src="https://alexander.kirk.at/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/git-branch-1.png" alt="" title="git-branch-1" width="228" height="105" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-336" /><br />
but I don&#8217;t want to push to origin/master but rather create a new branch. (Of course this works for any other branch, not named master)</p>
<p>So you can use <strong>this sequence of commands</strong>:</p>
<p><code>git checkout -b <i>newbranch</i><br />
git push origin <i>newbranch</i><br />
git checkout master<br />
git reset --hard origin/master</code></p>
<p>Explanation: This&#8230;</p>
<p>1. creates a new branch pointing to the current changes (and switches to it)<br />
<img data-attachment-id="335" data-permalink="https://alexander.kirk.at/2012/02/15/git-tip-changing-your-mind-push-pending-changes-to-a-not-yet-existing-new-branch/git-branch-2/" data-orig-file="https://alexander.kirk.at/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/git-branch-2.png" data-orig-size="228,105" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;}" data-image-title="git-branch-2" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://alexander.kirk.at/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/git-branch-2.png" data-large-file="https://alexander.kirk.at/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/git-branch-2.png" loading="lazy" src="https://alexander.kirk.at/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/git-branch-2.png" alt="" title="git-branch-2" width="228" height="105" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-335" /></p>
<p>2. pushes this new branch including the changes to the server<br />
<img data-attachment-id="339" data-permalink="https://alexander.kirk.at/2012/02/15/git-tip-changing-your-mind-push-pending-changes-to-a-not-yet-existing-new-branch/git-branch-3/" data-orig-file="https://alexander.kirk.at/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/git-branch-3.png" data-orig-size="257,103" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;}" data-image-title="git-branch-3" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://alexander.kirk.at/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/git-branch-3.png" data-large-file="https://alexander.kirk.at/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/git-branch-3.png" loading="lazy" src="https://alexander.kirk.at/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/git-branch-3.png" alt="" title="git-branch-3" width="257" height="103" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-339" /></p>
<p>3. switches back to the branch master<br />
4. and undoes the changes that were made locally<br />
<img data-attachment-id="333" data-permalink="https://alexander.kirk.at/2012/02/15/git-tip-changing-your-mind-push-pending-changes-to-a-not-yet-existing-new-branch/git-branch-4/" data-orig-file="https://alexander.kirk.at/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/git-branch-4.png" data-orig-size="228,105" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;}" data-image-title="git-branch-4" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://alexander.kirk.at/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/git-branch-4.png" data-large-file="https://alexander.kirk.at/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/git-branch-4.png" loading="lazy" src="https://alexander.kirk.at/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/git-branch-4.png" alt="" title="git-branch-4" width="228" height="105" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-333" /></p>
<p>The important thing to know is that the changes remain in the repository because a branch is merely a pointer to a commit.</p>
<p>Afterwards you can continue to commit to master, for example:<br />
<img data-attachment-id="345" data-permalink="https://alexander.kirk.at/2012/02/15/git-tip-changing-your-mind-push-pending-changes-to-a-not-yet-existing-new-branch/git-branch-5/" data-orig-file="https://alexander.kirk.at/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/git-branch-5.png" data-orig-size="237,119" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;}" data-image-title="git-branch-5" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://alexander.kirk.at/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/git-branch-5.png" data-large-file="https://alexander.kirk.at/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/git-branch-5.png" loading="lazy" src="https://alexander.kirk.at/wp-content/uploads/2012/02/git-branch-5.png" alt="" title="git-branch-5" width="237" height="119" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-345" /></p>
<p>(screenshots done with a fork of <a href="http://rowanj.github.com/gitx/">gitx</a>)</p>
            </div><!-- .entry-content -->
